OL,4,Cservices reform
OL,6,FThe minister said there were actions
OL,7,Fhe could take with the current
OL,8,Fallocation but said "significant
OL,9,Fadditional resources" will be required
OL,10,Ffor further actions in the years ahead.
OL,12,F"While the Programme for Government
OL,13,Fsets out the limits that the present
OL,14,Fbudgetary situation places on efforts
OL,15,Fto reduce waiting lists, I will
OL,16,Fcontinue to make the case for
OL,17,Fsignificantly more funding for
OL,18,Fhealth," he added.
